Reasoning: The paper discusses the IEEE 802.11 wireless LAN technology, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the physical layer standard for implementing wireless LAN, which involves signal processing and modulation techniques, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of wireless LAN technology in various devices such as cellphones and MP3 players, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also briefly discusses security issues related to wireless LAN, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of wireless broadband technologies on the market, which falls under the category of computer science and society (cs.COM).
